202510070057174021	Ẩn dụ trong câu "who has read the inside of the top of the box"	<p>We are all throwing the dice, playing the game, moving our pieces around the board, but if there is a problem, the lawyer is the only person <strong>who has</strong> <strong>read the inside of the top of the box.</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Hộp đồ chơi hay có hướng dẫn ở nắp hộp -&gt; Luật sư là người nắm rõ luật lệ và quy tắc</p>\n
202510080209499571	Words about watercraft	<p><strong>1. Các từ chỉ thuyền</strong></p>\n<p>Vessel = Tàu thuyền nói chung, chỉ phương tiện di chuyển trên mặt nước.</p>\n<p>Ship = Thuyền to</p>\n<p>Boat = Thuyền nhỏ, có thể được ship chứa</p>\n<p>Barge = Xà lan, thuyền phẳng</p>\n<p>Ferry = Ship chuyên chở khách/hàng hóa, chuyên môn hóa cho dịch vụ</p>\n<p>Yacht = Ship giải trí, đua thuyền. Có giá đắt đỏ.</p>\n<p>Canoe = Xuồng</p>\n<p>Raft = Bè</p>\n<p>Dinghy = Thuyền bé, thường được làm bằng cao su bơm hơi</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>2. Các bộ phận thuyền</strong></p>\n<p>Sail = Cánh buồm</p>\n<p>Mast = Cột buồm</p>\n<p>Hull = Thân tàu</p>\n<p>Desk = Boon tàu, sàn tàu</p>\n<p>Keel = Phần đáy tàu, nhô dài ra để giữ thăng bẳng</p>\n<p>Bow = Mũi tàu</p>\n<p>Stern = Đuôi tàu</p>\n<p>Rudder = Bánh lái tàu</p>\n<p>Paddle / Oar = Mái chèo</p>\n<p>Anchor = Mỏ neo</p>\n<p>Rigging = Hệ thống dâu buồm</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>3. Các hoạt động</strong></p>\n<p>Sailing = Đi thuyền buồn</p>\n<p>Voyage = Chuyến đi biển dài</p>\n<p>Cruise = Du ngoạn bằng tàu</p>\n<p>Embark = Lên tàu</p>\n<p>Disembark = Rời tàu</p>\n<p>Set sail = Nhổ neo, khởi hành</p>\n<p>Dock/Habour/Port = Bến cảng</p>\n<p>Fleet = Hạm đội tàu</p>\n
202510081615483565	Words about magnet	<p><strong>Magnet </strong>(n): nam châm</p>\n<p>- A magnet can attract iron</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Magnetic </strong>(adj): có từ tính</p>\n<p>- Iron is magnetic</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Magnetism </strong>(n): hiện tượng từ tính</p>\n<p>- Magnetism allows compasses to work</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Magnetized </strong>(v): bị từ hóa</p>\n<p>- The needle is magnetized</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Magnetomotive </strong>(adj): có liên quan tới lực điện từ</p>\n<p>- The coil generates a magnetomotive force when current flows</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510090148212853	Speaking notes 2: How to say "I love food"	<p>I adore trying new dishes.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm really into Asian dishes lately.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm crazy about Vietnamese foods.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm a big fan of trying new foods.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I enjoy discovering different local dishes while traveling</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Spicy food is my thing.</p>\n<p></p>\n<blockquote>Example1: I like to eating all kind of meat dishes. And I'm crazy about ground meat.</blockquote>\n<blockquote>- like + to V</blockquote>\n<blockquote>- live + Ving</blockquote>\n<blockquote>- Đang sử dụng số nhiều thì all kind -&gt; all kinds</blockquote>\n<blockquote>- Corrected: I like to eat all kinds of meat dishes. And I'm crazy about ground meat.</blockquote>\n
202510090235493926	Speaking notes 1	<p><strong>Trả lời câu hỏi với &gt;= 2 câu, có ví dụ hoặc lý do tại sao.</strong></p>\n<p>Q: Do you work or are you a student?</p>\n<p>A: I'm searching for a job now, and my previous job is a software developer in a financial company named FSS.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Review:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Đã có 2 câu (tôi đang tìm việc, việc làm trước đây của tôi)</p>\n<p>- Đã có ví dụ là đã làm ở công ty FSS</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Cấu trúc thời gian: first -&gt; then -&gt; after that -&gt; finally</strong></p>\n<p>Q: Describe a memorable journey you have taken.</p>\n<p>A:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- I remember this amazing trip to Da Nang city with my friends.</p>\n<p>- First we flew from Nội Bài airport to Da Nang city with Bamboo airline, the view from the plane was very beautiful, I could see layers of fluffy white clouds below us. This was a memorable experience for someone who rarely flies like me.</p>\n<p>- Then we booked a hotel near Mỹ Khê beach, and after checking in, we immediately went for swimming. I once read an article about Mỹ Khê is one of the ten most beautiful beaches in Asia and it's not exaggerated. The water is clean and crystal clear, the sand is white and smooth, and there's no trash could be found. This beach is definitely a must-to-go when you come Da Nang.</p>\n<p>- After that we visited Ngũ Hành Sơn mountain, which is a group of five limestone peaks. There are several temples and caves there, and it has a highest point which we can see the whole Da Nang city from there. Then we leaved for lunch and rented motobikes to explore city. On the final day we visited Hội An nightmarket, the entire market come with the glowing of hundreds coloful lanterns, and you could find everything from foods and handicrafts to clothes and souvenirs...</p>\n<p>- Finally, we flew back to Ha Noi and that was one of my unforgettable memories. Definitely I will come to Da Nang again someday.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510090627004047	Linking words	<p><strong>1. Adding ideas</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>and = và</p>\n<p>- apple <em><ins>and </ins></em>orange</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>also = và</p>\n<p>- I'm cold and I'm <em><ins>also </ins></em>hungry</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>as well as = cũng như là</p>\n<p>- We need to thinking about the timing <em><ins>as well as</ins></em> the cost</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>moreover = hơn thế nữa là, vế sau quan trọng hơn vế trước</p>\n<p>- The whole report is badly written. <em><ins>Moreover</ins></em>, it's inaccurate. (nếu muốn nhấn mạnh là ít nhất report phải đúng)</p>\n<p>- The policy is unfair. <em><ins>Moreover</ins></em>, it violates human rights.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>futhermore = hơn thế nữa là, vế sau ngang hàng vế trước</p>\n<p>- The whole report is badly written. <em><ins>Futhermore</ins></em>, it's inaccurate. (nếu muốn chỉ ra là report có nhiều sai sót là badly written + inaccurate)</p>\n<p>- The hotel offers free breakfast. <em><ins>Futhermore</ins></em>, guests can use the swinmming pool.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>in addition = ngoài ra thì = as well as</p>\n<p>- She is a fitness instructor in addition to being a full-time student</p>\n<p>- In addition being a full-time student, she is a fitness instructor</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>beside = bên cạnh đó</p>\n<p>- She won't mind if you're late - besides, it's hardly your fault</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>not only</p>\n<p>- Not only she is a student but she also is a fitness instructor</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>2. Constrating ideas</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>but = nhưng mà</p>\n<p>- I used to run very fast but now I can't</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>however = cho dù sao đi nữa</p>\n<p>- However hungry I am, I never seem to be able to finish off a whole pizza</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>although = mặc dù</p>\n<p>- Although it rained, we continued the game</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>though = nhưng, mặc dù, như thể, mặc dù thực tế là</p>\n<p>- You look as though you're been running a marathon (như thể)</p>\n<p>- They're comming next week, though I don't know which day (nhưng)</p>\n<p>- She hasn't called, even though she said she would</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>even though = mặc dù</p>\n<p>- Even though he left school at 16, he still managed to become prime minister</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>whereas = trong khi</p>\n<p>- He like dogs, whereas I like cats</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>while = trong khi</p>\n<p>- While I enjoy spending time in the city, I prefer living in the countryside</p>\n<p>- I like coffee, while my sister prefers tea</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>on the other hand</p>\n<p>- My husband likes classical music - I, on the other hand, like all kinds</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>3. Cause and Effect</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>because</p>\n<p>- I stayed home because it rained</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>since</p>\n<p>- Since you've already finished your work, you can leave early</p>\n<p>- We didn't go out since we don't have any money</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>as</p>\n<p>- As it was getting late, we decided to go home</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>due to = bởi vì điều gì đó</p>\n<p>- A lot of her unhappiness is due to boredom</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510100446459122	Speaking questions about work	<p><strong>1. Do you have a job right now?</strong></p>\n<p>- Yes I do, I'm working as software developer for a financial company named FSS. I really enjoy it because it lets me using coding skills to solve real life problems everydays. (Trả lời trọng tâm + Đưa ví dụ + Nêu cảm xúc)</p>\n<p>- I don't because I'm still a university student and I'm just focus on my studies right now.</p>\n<p>- No, not at the moment. I recently left my previous job and I'm looking for a new opportunity</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>2. Do you enjoy your job?</strong></p>\n<p>- Yes, because my job is creating a bond trading platform and it combines two things I like - coding and math.</p>\n<p>- Not much, the workload is heavy sometimes but I'm learning a lot from it.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>3. What responsibilities do you have at work?</strong></p>\n<p>- Structure: Your position -&gt; 2 - 4 main tasks -&gt; Addition tasks</p>\n<p>- I'm a software developer and my main tasks are maintain web application, fix bugs and collaborate with teams to improve performance. And I also testing new features before it release to customer.</p>\n<p>- My role is a software engineer and<strong> I'm in charge of </strong>design web application, build new features, improve performance if something is slow. And I also help train new staff members when they needs.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>4. What is your typical day like at work?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>5. What would you change about your job?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>6. What job do you think you will be doing in five years?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>7. What skills and qualifications are required for this job?</p>\n
202510121540475001	Writing note 1: Discussion essay	<p><strong>Question:</strong> Some people think that zoos are cruel and should be closed down. Others, however, believe that zoos can be useful in protecting wild animals.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Structure:</strong></p>\n<p>- Introduction</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Paraphrase question</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Giving opinion</p>\n<p>- Idea 1</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Câu chủ đề: On the one hand, ...</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Giải thích sao ý tưởng này được ủng hộ</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Đưa ra ví dụ</p>\n<p>- Idea 2</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Câu chủ đề: On the other hand, ...</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Giải thích sao ý tưởng này được ủng hộ</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Đưa ra ví dụ</p>\n<p>- Conclusion</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Paraphrase question: In conclusion, ...</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Giving opinion</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Các mẫu câu so sánh 2 quan điểm:</strong></p>\n<p>- Some people think ..., while others believe ...</p>\n<p>- Some argue that ..., wheas others claim that ...</p>\n<p>- It is believed by some that ..., while others hold the view that</p>\n<p>- While some believe that ..., others argues that ...&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- While certain people think that ..., others take the opposite view, ...</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Paraphrase question:</strong></p>\n<p>- Các từ khóa theo ý tưởng ủng hộ:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ benefical for the preservation of widlife</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ contribute to the protection of endangered species</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ conserving wildlife</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ animal conservation</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ help to preserve wild creatures</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ useful in protecting wildlife animals</p>\n<p>- Các từ khóa theo ý không ủng hộ:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ unethical/cruel/inhumane</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ should be banned/abolished/ shut down</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ immoral institutions</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ ought to be closed</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ call for their closure</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Example 1: Some people think that zoos are contribute to protection of wildlife animals, while others say that it's unethical and should be closed.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Cấu trúc: Some A think..., while B say...</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Example 2: People argue that zoos help to preserve endangered species. Others, however, believe that zoos are immoral institutions and ought to be banned</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Cấu trúc: A argue that .... B, however, believe ...&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Giving opinion structure</strong></p>\n<p>- I believe that ... / I think that ... / I feel that ...</p>\n<p>- It is my belief that ... / It is my opinion that ... / It is my view that ...</p>\n<p>- From my perspective ...</p>\n<p>- In my view, ...</p>\n<p>- Personally, I believe that ...</p>\n<p>- I strongly/firmly believe that ...</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Example 1: I believe that keeping animals in cages is immoral</p>\n<p>Example 2: It is my belief that zoos should definitely be banned</p>\n<p>Example 3: Despite/In spite of its benefits, I strongly believe that zoos should be closed</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Despite + N, In spite of + N</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Example Introduction</strong></p>\n<p>- Some argue that zoos <em><ins>are contribute</ins></em> to the <em><ins>conversation </ins></em>of endangered animals, while others believe that zoos are immoral and should be banned. <em><ins>I believe</ins></em> that <em><ins>despite of its</ins></em> benefits, zoos should definitely be shut down.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Bỏ are vì contribute đã là động từ rồi: zoos contribute to ...</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ conversation -&gt; cuộc trò chuyên &lt;&gt; conservation -&gt; bảo tồn</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ despite bỏ of</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ despite their benefits (zoos = số nhiều &lt;&gt; its số ít)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Thêm Personally trước I believe để tự nhiên hơn</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Body 1</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Lợi ích của sở thú:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Bảo vệ động vật khỏi săn bắn: protect animals from being hunted by poachers</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Bảo vệ động vật khỏi thay đổi khí hậu, thay đổi môi trường: protect animals from climate changes, natural habitats destroyed</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Nghiên cứu và nhân giống động vật: Research and breading programs to help reproduce population of animals</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Bảo vệ, cứu trợ động vật bị thương, mồ côi: Provide food, medical, shelter for injuried, sick animals or orphaned animals</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Đưa ra ví dụ: For example, last month I went to Thủ Lệ Zoo in Ha Noi, where I saw Indochiese tigers which are listed in Red Book being raised in good condition.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Example 1: On the one hand, zoos are keeping animals from being hunted by poachers and protecting animals from natural habitats destroyed. In addition, there are breading programs to help reproduce populations of endangered animals. Futher more, sicked or injuried animals received food, medical and shelter in zoos. For example, last month when I went to Thủ Lệ Zoo in Ha Noi, where I saw Indochiese tigers which are listed in Red Book being raised in good condition.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ are keeping -&gt; help protect (chung hơn)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ from natural habitats destroyed -&gt; from the destruction of their natural habitats (tự nhiên hơn)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ breading programs -&gt; breeding programs (sai từ)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ to help reprocedure populations -&gt; that aim to increase the populations (tự nhiên hơn)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ sicked (verb) -&gt; sick (adj) (cần dùng tính từ,  sicked up = động từ)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ medical -&gt; medical care (adj + noun)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Indochiese -&gt; Indochinese</p>\n<p>Review 1: On the one hand, zoos help protect animals from begin hunted by poachers and protecting animals from the destruction of their natural habitats. In addition, there are breeding programs that ami to increase the populations of endangered animals. Futhermore, sick or injuried animals received food, medical care and shelter in zoos. For example, last month when I went to Thủ Lệ Zoo in Ha Noi, where I saw Indochinese tigers which are listed in Red Book being raised in good condition.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Body 2</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Tác hại của sở thú (zoos are cruel):</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Động vật không được tự do: Animals lose their freedom. They can't freely run, hunt or communicate with other.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Điều kiện sống không tự nhiên, chật hẹp: Unnatural living conditions, cramped capes, little space to move</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Tâm lý đau khổ: Stress, depression because being in capes for too long. Zoochosis.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Đưa ra ví dụ: For instance, animals such as elephants or lions are forced to perform tricks for visitors, whichs is unnatural and stressful for them.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Example: On the other hand, animals in zoos are lose their freedom because they can't freely run, hunt or even communicate with other animals. They live under horrible conditions, cramped capes and have little space to move. More over, animals being in caped for a long time result in being stress, depression. A term called "Zoochosis" describe a phychological distress where animals doing repetitve behaviors due captivity. For instance, in zoos, animals such as elephans or lions are forced to perform tricks for visitors which are unnatural and stressful for them.</p>\n<p>- are lose -&gt; lose (thừa động từ are)</p>\n<p>- cramped capes -&gt; cramped cages</p>\n<p>- More over -&gt; Moreover</p>\n<p>- phychological -&gt; psychological</p>\n<p>- doing repetitve behaviors due captivity -&gt; doing/perform repetitive behaviors due to captivity (thiếu giới từ to)</p>\n<p>- elephans -&gt; elephants</p>\n<p>- animals being in caped -&gt; animals being kept in captivity</p>\n<p>- result in being stress, depression -&gt; result in stress and depression (result in + N)</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Review: On the other hand, animals in zoos lose their freedom because they can't freely run, hunt or even communicate with other animals. They live under horrible conditions, cramped cages and have little space to move. Moreover, animals being kept in captivity for a long time result in stressful and depression. A term called "Zoochosis" decribes a psychological distress where animals doing repetitive behaviors like pacing, biting fences and even self harm. Some zoos treat animals as tools for entertainment and making money from them. For instance, in zoos, animals such as elephents or lions are forced to perform tricks for visitors which are unnatural and stressful for them.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Conclusion</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Sử dụng các từ kết luận:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ In conclusion, while some people believe that A, other think that B. Personally, I believe that C, because of D.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Example 1: In conclusion, while people believe that zoo should be kept because it can help conserving wildlife. Personally I think zoos should be close down because the suffer it bring to animals is unacceptable.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ the suffer -&gt; the suffering (the + N)</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Example 2: To sum up, despite the benefits that zoos may bring, I believe that closing them is an ethical choice for both animals and humans.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Cấu trúc: N + may bring</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Một số câu có thể dùng cho đề bài chủ đề "zoo":</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510140100406324	Writing note 2: Letter of advice	<p><strong>Question</strong>: Recently you saw an article in a newspaper/journal about a city/town you know and some of the information in the article was incorrect. Write a letter to the editor regarding this.</p>\n<p>In your letter, you should tell:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>how you know about this city/town</li>\n<li>what information was incorrect</li>\n<li>what the editor should do about this.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Answer:</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Dear Sir or Madam,</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm wrote this letter to you because I noticed on your newspaper there is incorrect information about Son La province. And I would like to giving some suggest to correct it.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Firstly, to introduce, I have been living in Son La for my whole life. And I know it like the back of my hand. In your recent newpaper, you wrote Son La is not the origin of dried buffalo meat which is incorrect. I have ate this dishes since a child and I have heard local people talking about how to make it.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Secondly, I think it is important to correct this information as soon as possible, because it may confuse readers.&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm looking forward to hearing back from you,</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Best regards,&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Hoang Le Luong</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Review grammar:</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- information = danh từ không đếm được (không cần dùng an)</p>\n<p>- I'm wrote this letter -&gt; I'm writing this letter (thì hiện tại tiếp diễn để chỉ một mục đích)</p>\n<p>- on your newpaper -&gt; in your newpaper/article (dùng in với newpaper/article)</p>\n<p>- to giving some suggest -&gt; to give some suggestions (to + V; some + noun prural)</p>\n<p>- newpaper -&gt; newspaper</p>\n<p>- I have ate -&gt; I have eaten</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I eat, she eats (present)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I ate, she ate (past)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I have/has/had eaten (perfect)</p>\n<p>- this dishes -&gt; this dish (this + noun singular)</p>\n<p>- since a child -&gt; since I was a child (thiếu chủ ngữ và động từ)</p>\n<p>- you wrote Son La that is -&gt; you wrote that Son La is not (mệnh đề tường thuật)</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Dear Sir or Madam,</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm writing this letter to you because I noticed in your newspaper there is incorrect information about Son La province. And I would like to give some suggestions to correct it.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Firstly, I have been living in Son La my whole life. And I know it like the back of my hand. In your recent newspaper, you wrote Son La that is not the origin of dried buffalo meat which is incorrect. I have eaten this dish since I was a child and I have heard local people talking about how to make it.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Secondly, I think it is important to correct this information as soon as possible because it may confuse readers.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm looking forward to hearing back from you.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Best regards,</p>\n<p>Hoang Le Luong</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Review writing:</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- I'm writing this letter to you because I noticed in your newspaper there is incorrect information about Son La province. And I would like to give some suggestions to correct it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ because -&gt; regarding = about, relating to</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* Your recent letter regarding the above proposal</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* The company is beging questioned regarding its employment policy</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ incorrect information -&gt; inaccurate information, misleading information</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* contains misleading information</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ in your newspaper -&gt; in you recent article</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* one newspaper have mutiple article</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I noticed -&gt; I came across/ I found/ I observed</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ give some -&gt; offer a few, provide some information</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Có thể bỏ And khi bắt đầu câu để sang trọng hơn</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Rewrite: I'm writing this letter to you regarding an article in your recent newpaper that contains misleading information. I would like to offer a few suggestions to correct it.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Firstly, I have been living in Son La my whole life. And I know it like the back of my hand. In your recent newspaper, you wrote Son La that is not the origin of dried buffalo meat which is incorrect. I have eaten this dish since I was a child and I have heard local people talking about how to make it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ know it like the back of my hand</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* very familiar with it</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* know the area inside out</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* know the area very well</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ you wrote that ... -&gt; you state that ...</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ incorrect -&gt; inaccurate, wrong, inexact, false, mistaken, imprecise</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ people talking about how to make it -&gt; people talking about how it is made (active to passive)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Không bắt đầu câu bằng And vì kém sang</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ people talking about how to make it</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* This dish has been prepared and enjoyed by local people for generations</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* This dish has been part of our local culture for generations</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Rewrite: Firstly, I have been living in Son La my whole life. And I know the area inside out. In your recent newspaper, you stated that Son La is not the origin of dried buffalo meat which is inaccurate. This dish has been part of our local culture for generations and I have eaten this since I was a child.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Note: I, we, you + have. He, she, it + has</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510140118012528	Writing note 3: Task 1 General	<p>&nbsp;Two type of style:</p>\n<p>- If it is writing a letter to friend then it is informal</p>\n<p>- Else it is formal</p>\n<p>- Don't have semi-formal to ielts</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Begin letter:</p>\n<p>- Formal: Dear Sir or Madam,</p>\n<p>- Informal: Dear (any name),</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Structure of letter:</p>\n<p>- Purpose: Writing about why we write this letter</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510140807167882	Writing note 4: Câu mở đầu đoạn văn	<p>Nêu luận điểm A và luận điểm B không đối lập nhau</p>\n<p>- To begin with</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ To begin with, the goverment should invest more in public transport</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ To begin with, zoos help protect animals by provide shelter for them</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ To begin with, transportation vehicles are less polution than private vehicles</p>\n<p>- Furthermore</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ The house is beautiful. Furthermore, it's in a great location.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I don't know what happened to Romeo. Furthermore, I don't care.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Furthermore, we make the hypothesis that the radiation source is optically thin</p>\n<p>- In addition</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ In addition to his apartment in Manhattan, he has a vila in Italy and a castle in Scotland</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ She is a fitness instructor in addition to being a fulltime student.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ In addition to looking after the baby, she has been continuing with her studies</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*In addition, Subject + Verb + Object</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*In addition to something&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- One major reason is that</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ One major reason is that government does things it has no business doing</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ One major reason is that they create rules for people.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ One major reason is that medician is challenging.</p>\n<p>- The first point to consider is that</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ The first point to consider is that food sequencing has a significant impact on glucose and insulin levels</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ The first point to consider is that people vary a lot in their abilities to learn at any age</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ The first point to consider is that our childrent have already learned a great deal about how to manage their relationships with others</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*orther + N = others</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*others = other people</p>\n<p>- Another significant point is that</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Nêu luận điểm A và B đối lập nhau</p>\n<p>- On the one hand</p>\n<p>- On the other hand</p>\n<p>- However it could also be argued that</p>\n<p>- In contrast</p>\n<p>- Conversely</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Đưa ra ví dụ:</p>\n<p>- For example</p>\n<p>- For instance</p>\n<p>- To illustrate</p>\n<p>- A good example of this is</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Kết luận:</p>\n<p>- In conclusion</p>\n<p>- To sum up</p>\n<p>- Overall</p>\n<p>- All things considered</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Ví dụ:</p>\n<p>- To begin with, abc xyz. Futher more, abc xyz.</p>\n<p>- On the other hand, abc xyz. Nevertheless, abc xyz</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510141530205101	Writing note 5: Write a letter to ask for room change	<p><strong>Question</strong>: You live in a room in college which you share with another student. However, there are many problems with this arrangement and you find it very difficult to work.</p>\n<p>Write a letter to the accommodation officer at the college. In the letter,</p>\n<p>• describe the situation</p>\n<p>• explain your problems and why it is difficult to work</p>\n<p>• say what kind of accommodation you would prefer</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Answer</strong>:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>//Lý do: Phòng quá nhỏ cho 2 người, muốn chuyển tới phòng đơn</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Dear Sir or Madam,</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm a student at room 101 and have student id is ABC123. I'm writing this letter for you to address a problem which me and my roommate are facing, which is our room is too small.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>To begin with, our room can only fit a desk, a table and a bed for both of us to sleep on. When we need to study, one must study on bed while the other one use the table. Moreover,  the bed is too short, I was 180cm tall so my feets are hanging out of the bed. In addition, because of narrow space, we can't avoid to slam into each other sometimes when moving.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>From inconvenients I listed above, I would like to asking for switching to another room. A single room with a windows is nice, I wouldn't mind paying more for monthly fee.&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm looking forward to hearing soon from you.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Best regards,</p>\n<p>Hoang Le Luong</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Grammar review:</strong></p>\n<p>- living at -&gt; living in</p>\n<p>- and have student id (thiếu chủ ngữ)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; and my student id is</p>\n<p>- I'm writing this letter for you to address a problem <strong>which </strong>me and my roommate are facing, <strong>which </strong>is our room is too small.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ which đầu tiên đúng</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ which thứ hai thiếu từ liên kết với "problem"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; which is that our room is too small</p>\n<p>- me and my roommate</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Dùng me khi me là tân ngữ</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Dùng I khi I là chủ ngữ</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Tôi và bạn cùng phòng của tôi đang đối mặt với vấn đề -&gt; Dùng I vì là chủ ngữ</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; my roommate and I</p>\n<p>- which is our room is too small (hai động từ is)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; which is that our room is too small&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; which our room is too small</p>\n<p>- one must stay on bed and other one use the table</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; one must stay on <strong>the </strong>bed and other one <strong>uses </strong>the table</p>\n<p>- the bed is too short, I was 180cm tall so my feets are hanging out of the bed.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Tách thành 2 câu</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ feet = số nhiều của foot</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ 2 động từ are và hanging out</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; the bad is too short. I was 180cm tall, so my feet hang out of the bed.</p>\n<p>- "because of narrow space, we can't avoid to slam into each other sometimes when moving."</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Thiếu the trước narray space</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ avoid + V-ing</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ slamming (mạnh) và bumping (nhẹ hơn, va chạm nhẹ)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Cụm từ hay dùng: moving around</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; because of the narrow space, we can't avoid bumping into each other sometimes when moving around</p>\n<p>- "From inconvenients I listed above..."</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ inconvenient = tính từ không phải danh tiwf</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ inconveniences = danh từ</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; From the inconveniences I listed above ...</p>\n<p>- "I would like to asking for switching to another room."</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ to + V</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; I would like to ask for switching to another room</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; I would like to ask to switch to another room (ask for V-ing là không tự nhiên, thay bằng ask to V)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; I would like to ask for a room change (ask for + N tự nhiên hơn)</p>\n<p>- "A single room with a windows is nice..."</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ a windows -&gt; a window</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; A single room with a window is nice</p>\n<p>- for monthly fee</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; for the monthly fee</p>\n<p>- I'm looking forward to hearing soon from you.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&gt; Câu phổ biến hơn: I'm looking forward to hearing from you soon</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Rewrite for grammar fix:</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Dear Sir or Madam,</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm a student living in room 101, and my student ID is ABC123. I'm writing this letter to address a problem which my roommate and I are facing, which is that our room is too small.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>To begin with, our room can only fit a desk, a table and a bed for both of us to sleep on. When we need to study, one must study on the bed while the other one uses the table. Moreover, the bed is too short. I am 180cm tall, so my feet hang out of the bed. In addition, because of the narrow space, we can't avoid bumping into each other sometimes when moving around.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>From the inconveniences I listed above, I would like to ask for a room change. A single room with a window is nice. I wouldn't mind paying more for the monthly fee.&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm looking forward to hearing from you soon.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Best regards,</p>\n<p>Hoang Le Luong</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Addition suggestion:</strong></p>\n<p>- Thư xin, nhờ thì sử dụng cấu trúc sau:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I would be grateful if ...</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I looking forward to your kind consideration</p>\n<p>- Sử dụng thêm các từ nối: Furthermore, In addition, Given these problems</p>\n<p>- Sử dụng các từ nâng cao:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ small space -&gt; limited space</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ room -&gt; accommodate</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ unconfortable</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ affects my sleep quality</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ inconvenient</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ consideration</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ some problems -&gt; some difficulties</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ are facing -&gt; are experiencing&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Sử dụng cấu trúc: Nêu ra vấn đề -&gt; Hậu quả về mặt vật lý -&gt; Hậu quả về mặt tinh thần, chất lượng sống</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Dear Sir or Madam,</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm a student living in room 103 and my student ID is ABC123. I'm writing this letter to address some difficulties which my roommate and I are experiencing right now, due to the limited space in our room.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>To begin with, our room is so small that it can only accommodate one desk, one table and a single bed for both of us to rest on. This makes studying uncomfortable because if one person is use the table then the other one will have to study on bed.  Furthermore, the bed is little compare to me. I'm 180cm tall so my feet often hang out, which affects my sleep quality. Moreover, one small bed for both person is painful to just by laying down. Beside that, when moving around we sometime bumping into each other which is very inconvenient.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Giving these problems, I would be grateful if I you consider moving me out to another room. A single room with a window is perfect, and I willing to pay a higher monthly fee if necessary.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I'm looking forward to hearing from you soon.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Best regards,</p>\n<p>Hoang Le Luong</p>\n<p></p>\n
202510150220586038	Writing note 6: Nursing home	<p><strong>Question</strong>: In Britain, when someone gets old they often go to live in a home with other old people where there are nurses to look after them. Sometimes the government has to pay for this care. Who do you think should pay for this care, the government or the family? Give reasons for your answer and include any relevant examples from your own knowledge or experience.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Keywords</strong>:</p>\n<p>- Chủ đề chính = elderly care = chăm sóc cho người già</p>\n<p>- Người cao tuổi: elderly people, the elderly, senior citizens, older adults</p>\n<p>- Viện dưỡng lão: nursing home, care home, retirement home</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ nursing home = người già cần chăm sóc y tế</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ retirement home = người già không cần chăm sóc y tế thường xuyên</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Hai từ nursing home, retirement home có thể thay thế nhau</p>\n<p>- Home care = chăm sóc người già tại nhà</p>\n<p>- Comminity care = chăm sóc người già tại các cơ sở như viện dưỡng lão, bệnh viện...</p>\n<p>- Khía cạnh ai trả tiền:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ government funding, public funds</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ taypayer's money, social welfare, social security (an sinh xã hội)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ family responsibility, filial (hiếu thảo) duty, family support</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ personal savings, pension (lương hưu), retirement fund</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ financial burden, economic pressure</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Các cụm hay dùng:</strong></p>\n<p>- The majority of retirees are</p>\n<p>- It is the goverment's duty to</p>\n<p>- Families should take responsibility for&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Public funding should be used to support</p>\n<p>- Caring for the elderly should not be a burden on</p>\n<p>- With the ageing population, society must find a balance between</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Ý tưởng gia đình nên là người chi trả các chi phí cho viện dưỡng lão:</strong></p>\n<p>- Gia đình nên trả vì họ sẽ quan tâm tới chất lượng dịch vụ -&gt; Họ sẽ tới xem xét cơ sở vật chất đồng thời thăm người già nhiều hơn</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ motivated to monitor = có động lực để xem xét&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ quality of services and staff = chất lượng dịch vụ và nhân viên</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ visit more often = tới thăm nhiều hơn</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ caregivers = người chăm sóc</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Example: wealthy families in US, Japan often choose private nursing homes</p>\n<p>- Gia đình nên trả vì họ sẽ tự chọn được viện dưỡng lão phù hợp theo điều kiện tài chính, y tế, văn hóa cụ thể</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ financial situation, culture values, comfort level, medical facilities</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Example: Asian families choose nursing homes with approximate food and religious activities</p>\n<p>- Gia đình nên trả vì đó là cách họ báo đáp cha mẹ, thể hiện lòng hiếu thảo</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ show respect</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ traditional family values</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ filial piety</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ gratitude toward</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Example: Asian cultures consider taking care for parents by living with them or paying for their care is moral duty for children</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Answer</strong>:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Nowadays, with the advanced technology and <em><ins>medician care (medicial care)</ins></em>, a large number of elderly people can live a comfortable life. But <em><ins>maintains these services (maintaining these services)</ins></em> for old people come with great cost, such as expensive medical equipments, <em><ins>nursing house (nursing home)</ins></em> and salary for people working in it. Some people the government should paying for the cost. Personally I argue that the families should take the responsibility and pay for the care of nursing house. The first reason that families can control the services quality that their elderly can receive. The second reason is the filial duty with their parents.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The first point is by paying for the nursing home cost, families are motivate to monitor the quality of services and staff. <em><ins>Their will likely (They are likely)</ins></em> to visit to communicate with caregivers and spend time with their elderly. <em><ins>Futher more (Furthermore)</ins></em>, some families has unique expectations for how their parents should be treated. By paying for the care themself, they can choose a suitable nursing home depend on financial situation, culture values and conform level. For example, wealthy families in the United States or Japan often choose luxuly private nursing home for their elderly.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The second point is about filial piety. Paying for the care of grandparents or parents is a way of showing <em><ins>respest (respect) </ins></em>and gratitude toward the people who raised us. It reflects the previous traditional family values such as love and responsibility. For instance, in Asian cultures, they consider taking care for their parents by living with them or paying for their care is a moral duty for children.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>To conclusion, while some people <em><ins>belive (believe) </ins></em>the cost of care for elderly in nursing home should be <em><ins>payed (paid) </ins></em>by the government, I believe that the families should the ones doing that responsibility. By our own paying, we can provide what the best for our elderly that no one can compares to.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- By our own paying -&gt; By paying for it ourself (bằng cách tự trả)&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Review answer:</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- So sánh giàu nghèo, sử dụng câu "In constract, ...":&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ In contrast, families with lower incomes may opt for smaller yet still reliable facilities, ensuring their loved ones receive personalized attention</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ opt (verb) = chọn</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ reliable facilities (các cơ sở đáng tin cậy)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ smaller yet still reliable facilities: Cấu trúc A yet still B</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ personalized attention = sự chăm sóc cá nhân hóa</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ their loved ones = thay thế cho the elderly, parents, grandparents</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Mở rộng ý về lòng hiếu thảo:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Tạo tiền đề cho thế hệ sau: When the children willingly to contribute financially, it sets a positive example for the next generation.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Củng cố quan hệ: When the children willingly to contribute financially, it strengthens emotional bonds within the family</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Kết quả:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* sense of duty = ý thức trách nhiệm</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* family cohesion = sự gắn kết của gia đình</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* reduces the dependence on the government</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* Sử  dụng câu mở đầu: In the long run, ...</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* In the long run, this sense of duty helps preserve family cohesion and reduces the dependence on the government.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Sentences</strong>:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Are </strong>taking care of elderly people a burden for families?</p>\n<p>- Taking care of = 1 hành động = số ít -&gt; Dùng Is</p>\n<p>-&gt; Is talking care of elderly people a burden for families?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Is looking after elderly people hard for families?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Is looking after old people a challenge for young people?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Does caring for elderly people put pressure on families?&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Note:</p>\n<p>- a burden for/on = một gánh nặng</p>\n<p>- hard = khó khăn cho</p>\n<p>- a challenge = một thử thách</p>\n<p>- put pressure on = đặt áp lực lên</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>People<strong> take care for </strong>their old parents because they love them, if they don't they will send their parents <strong>to nursing home.</strong></p>\n<p>- take care for -&gt; take care of someone = chăm sóc ai đó</p>\n<p>- old parents -&gt; elderly parents (lịch sự hơn)</p>\n<p>- to nursing home&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Số ít: to a nursing home</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Số nhiều: to nursing homes</p>\n<p>-&gt; Viết lại: People take care of their old parents because they love them, if they don't they will send their parent to a nursing home.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>People looking after their elderly parents out of love and a sense of responsibility.</p>\n<p>- fall out of love = hết yêu</p>\n<p>- out of love = vì yêu</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>They take care of their parents out of filial duty</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Note:</p>\n<p>- take care of = chăm sóc ai đó</p>\n<p>- take care = cẩn thận</p>\n<p>- take care for = cẩn thận vì điều gì đó</p>\n<p>- take care for yourself = cẩn thận vì bản thân</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Some nursing homes are bad because it have poor facilities and the staff even abuse the elderly.</p>\n<p>-&gt; các viện dưỡng lão -&gt; số nhiều -&gt; they have</p>\n<p>-&gt; Some nursing homes are bad because they have poor facilies and the staff even abuse the elderly.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Some nursing homes provide poor care because they lack proper facilities and well-trained staff.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Some nursing homes provide poor care because they lack proper facilities and well-trainned staff</p>\n<p>- are bad -&gt; provide poor care</p>\n<p>- poor facilites -&gt; lack proper facilities</p>\n<p>- the staff even abuse -&gt; well-trainned staff</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>If families are the one who paying the cost, then they will have more control about quality of services their elderly received. For example, rich families usually choose luxury private nursing homes to take care for their parents.</p>\n<p>- Số nhiều: the one -&gt; the ones</p>\n<p>- Chia đúng thì hiện tại đơn: who paying -&gt; who pay</p>\n<p>- Chi phí dịch vụ là số nhiều: the cost -&gt; the costs</p>\n<p>- Cụm đúng: have control over something (sửa control about -&gt; control over)</p>\n<p>- to take care for -&gt; to take care of</p>\n<p>- rich -&gt; wealthy (trang trọng hơn)</p>\n<p>- elderly received = người già được nhận vào đâu đó...</p>\n<p>- elderly receive = người già nhận dịch vụ -&gt; đúng hơn</p>\n<p>- Viết lại: If families are the ones pay the costs, then they will have more control over quality of services their elderly receive. For example, wealthy families usually choose luxury private nursing homes to take care of their parents.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510161332414939	Writing note 7: Analyse some samples	<p><strong>Question</strong>: It is a natural process for animal species to become extinct (e.g. Dinosaur, dodos …) There is no reason why people should try to prevent this from happening. Do you agree or disagree?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong>: Some people believe that there are no compelling reasons for us to protect animal species from extinction as it occurs naturally. I personally disagree with this conviction and will support my argument in the essay below.</p>\n<p>- compelling (có sức thuyết phục) reasons</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ convincing reasons</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ strong reasons, valid reasons</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ solid reasons</p>\n<p>- Rewrite: There are a lot of species that have become extinct, and the number keeps increasing day by day. Some people think that it is natural process, and we should not interfere. But I disagree for two main reasons. One reason is that I think it's important to maintain biodiversity and the second reason is because some animals became extinct by human, which is not a natural process.</p>\n
202510170553015368	Random Reddit Learning 1	<p>What was a core rule of "Old Internet" etiquette that is completely dead now?</p>\n<p>- etiquette (n) = phép lịch sự</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>It does give me a bit of delight seeing those on someone's neocities site.</p>\n<p>- neocities = web tạo web</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Rage bait feels way more insidious now though.</p>\n<p>- insidious (adj) = xảo quyệt</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I agree, now days with curated feeds and algorithmic for you.</p>\n<p>- curated (v) = chọn lọc</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Is it possible that the reason we haven't encountered intelligent life is because intelligent life isn't evolutionary viable?</p>\n<p>- viable (adj) = khả thi</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Do non-binary identities reenforce gender stereotypes?</p>\n<p>- reenforce (v) = củng cố, tăng cường</p>\n<p>- reinforce (v) = reenforce</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ The pockets on my jean are reinforce with double stitching</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- stereotypes (n) = định kiến, khuân mẫu</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I think I fit the popular stereotype of a mad scientist</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>And notorious child abuser!</p>\n<p>- notorious (adj) = két tiếng</p>\n<p>- Los Angeles is notorious for its smug</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>How realistic are movie-style “untouchable” criminal networks in modern developed countries?</p>\n<p>- realistic = practical, plausible</p>\n<p>- untouchable = immune / above the law</p>\n<p>- criminal networks = criminal organizations</p>\n<p>- mordern developed contries = developed nations</p>\n<p>-&gt; Pharaphrase: How plausible are movies featuring immune criminal organizations in developed nations?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Note: Một câu trong tiếng anh không thể có 1 chủ ngữ và 2 động từ</p>\n<p>- Ví dụ: Movies feature criminals are realistic</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Subject = Movies</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Verbs = feature, are</p>\n<p>- Sửa:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Movies that feature criminals are realistic (thêm that để có mệnh đề quan hệ)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Movies featuring criminals are realistic (cụm phân từ featuring = that feature)</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I am unsure whether I should disclose about my small size penis to my future spouse before marriage.</p>\n<p>- disclose (v) = tiết lộ</p>\n<p>- They disclosed her name the the press (hội báo chí)</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I am currently in a dilemma.</p>\n<p>- dilemma (n) = tình thế tiến thoái lưỡng nam</p>\n<p>- The people often face the dillemma of feeding themself of their cattle</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510191402499261	Phân biệt nor, either, neither	<p><strong>Either </strong>= one or other option</p>\n<p>- I like either tea or coffee</p>\n<p>- Either you come now or you will miss the bus</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Neither </strong>= not one and not the other option = negative of either</p>\n<p>- Neither option is good</p>\n<p>- Neither of them came</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Nor </strong>= join 2 negative clause</p>\n<p>- She didn't smile, nor did she speak</p>\n<p>- Neither the teacher nor the students are ready</p>\n
