202510201933160251	Writing note 7: Argumentative Essay	<p><strong>Question</strong>: Many factors motivate people in the workplace. Of these, money is the most important. To what extent do you agree or disagree?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Ideas</strong>:</p>\n<p>- Money is the key factor</p>\n<p>- Other factors also important</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong>: Motivation in workplace is affected by various factors. Including job satisfaction, career development, and monetary rewards. While money is an important motivator, I believe it is not always the most significant factor for all employees.</p>\n<p>+ Motivation factors, motivation elements, different aspects, various reasons.</p>\n<p>+ is affected, is influenced, largely depends, is determined</p>\n<p>+ Including, Such as, Ranging from ... to ..., Comprising</p>\n<p>+ Job satisfaction, job fulfillment</p>\n<p>+ career development, career advancement, career development opportunities, career progression, professional growth</p>\n<p>+ monetary rewards, financial rewards, finnancial incentives</p>\n<p>+ While abc, I believe xyz.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Many aspects affect motivation at work, such as job fulfillment, career development opportunities, and monetary rewards. While these are the key conditions when searching for a job, I believe money is the most important factor.</p>\n<p>- Note: Không dùng such as làm đầu câu</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Body </strong>1: Money is the key factor</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Financial rewards are crucial because they directly affect employee's standard of living and financial security. For instance, higher salaries often encourage employees to work harder and remain loyal to their company as they feel their efforts are fairly rewards.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Financial rewards are crucial because they .. = Monetary incentives play a vital role as they ...</p>\n<p>- They directly affect ... = They have a direct impact on ...&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Employee's standard of living = Employee's quality of life</p>\n<p>- Employee's financial security = Employee's economic stability</p>\n<p>-&gt; Monetary incentives play a vital role as they have a direct impact on employee's quality of life and economic stability.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- higher salaries = offering increased salaries</p>\n<p>- often encourage = can motivate</p>\n<p>- to work harder = to perform better</p>\n<p>- remain loyal the their company = stay commited to the organization</p>\n<p>- they feel their effects are fairly rewards = they perceive their contributions are justly recognized</p>\n<p>-&gt; For example, offering increased salaries can motivate employees to contribute better and stay commited to the organization as they perceive their contributions are justly recognized.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510210620197488	Random note 1	<p>I don't want to buy something and regret later.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I do some research before that. (Before buying new thing)</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Question -&gt; Many thing to answers -&gt; Choose one thing and take deeply about it.</p>\n<p>What do you like to do in your free time?</p>\n<p>- Answer directly: I like playing video game</p>\n<p>- What game: I mostly play Minecraft, it's very popular game. In that game, you can build stuff and do anything you want.</p>\n<p>- How many hours spend: I spend almost my childhood playing it.</p>\n<p>- Adding information: I introduce that game to my brother and he loves it.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Describe a skill that you took a long time to learn:</p>\n<p>-  The skill is be easy on myself</p>\n<p>- When you started learning it: When I was a teenager, I often felt ashamed of myself from past actions, but when I go to university, I started to forgive myself and don't think too much about people opinions.</p>\n<p>- How you learned it: I learned by talking to myself and considering what should be done and what should not. Back then, I usually read self-help books and watch ted talk and I think it shaped my thought about my feeling about myself.</p>\n<p>- Why it took a long time to learn: It took a long time to learn because it's the way who I am, I was a shy boy since a child and pay attention to people opinions too much. And changing ourself usually not a easy thing to do, so I think that it the reason.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Determination</p>\n<p>Talking feedback</p>\n<p>Clear communication</p>\n<p>Good enough to break the ice between people</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Question: Do you work or study?</p>\n<p>Answer: I am currently seeking employment. I used to work as a software developer. My job was to maintain a bond trading platform for users. Now, I am aiming for a similar position that pays better.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Question: How would you describe your style</p>\n<p>- Social gathering with my friends</p>\n<p>- I would like describe my style is simple and effective. I wear the same old clothes and shoes for years and rarely buy new ones.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Question: What influences your choices when buying clothes?</p>\n<p>- I choose my clothes based on one key factor — comfort. For example, I have big feet, so I must pick the largest shoe size in the store. And if a shirt or pair of pants doesn’t fit my body, even if it catches my eye, I don’t buy it.</p>\n<p>- Note: Quần = pants có số nhiều vì chỉ 2 ống quần</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ A pair of pants, two pair of pants</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Question: What influences your clothing choice?</p>\n<p>- My clothing choice is depends on where I'm going. For instance, if I go out with my friends then I would wear casual clothes. And if I have to go to work, I will wear formal clothes such as a white shirt and black trousers.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- some bracelets, some necklaces</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Question: What type of art do you prefer?</p>\n<p>- Listing art types: cinema, painting, drawing, music, ...</p>\n<p>- Direct answer: I like music</p>\n<p>- Art is a broad subject. Including cinema, drawing, painting, music. And music is the type of art I like the most.&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>They both go hand in hand.</p>\n<p>- Success and hard work go hand in hand</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>vague /vếg/ = không chắc chắn</p>\n<p>- He is very vague about his activites</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>There are 345 varieties of parrot in existence and, of these, one-sixth live in Australia.</p>\n<p>- Có 345 loài vẹt tồn tại. (Subject + are + object + adverb)</p>\n<p>- of these = trong số chúng (cụm giới từ để liên kết 2 mệnh đề)</p>\n<p>- on-sixth live in Australia = 1/6 sống ở nước Úc (S + live + adverb)</p>\n<p>- Cấu trúc: Fraction of noun -&gt; verb agrees with noun</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ One-sixth of 345 varieties of parrot (số nhiều) -&gt; verb = live</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510220800250320	Một số cụm chỉ thời gian	<p><strong>1. As early as</strong></p>\n<p>- As early as the 16th century, ... = Ngay từ thế kỷ thứ 16, ...</p>\n<p>- Nhấn mạnh sự sớm hơn dự kiến</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>2. As far back as</strong></p>\n<p>- As far back as the 16th century = Từ tận thế kỷ 16</p>\n<p>- Nhấn mạnh địa điểm đang nói rất xa</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>3. Since</strong></p>\n<p>- Since 1900</p>\n<p>- Một hành động bắt đầu quá khứ + tiếp diễn tới hiện tại</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>4. From ... onward</strong></p>\n<p>- From 2025 onward, all cars will be electric.</p>\n<p>- Một hành động bắt đầu + tiếp diễn sau đó (có thể tiếp diễn tới tương lai)</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>5. By the time</strong></p>\n<p>- By the 18th century, the printing press has spread across Europe</p>\n<p>- By the time he arrived, the meeting had already begun</p>\n<p>- Diễn tả một thời điểm mà trước đó đã có một hành động được thực hiện lâu rồi</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>6. As long ago as</strong></p>\n<p>- As long ago as 500 BC, people knew the earth was round</p>\n<p>- Diễn tả sự ngạc nhiên&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>7. As recently as</strong></p>\n<p>- As recently as 2010, few people owned smartphones</p>\n<p>- Note: few = thiếu, tiêu cực, a few = có một ít, tích cực</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510222054245649	Speaking: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4nrG6SHM-rY	<p><strong>1. Examiner</strong>: Let’s start off by talking about art. Do you like art?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Candidate</strong>: Growing up, art was a way for me to express myself and show my emotions through whatever medium I chose. I actually prefer art more than music in some ways. I like to paint, and I enjoy seeing how other people express themselves through their art as well. So yes, I do love art.</p>\n<p>- through whatever medium I chose -&gt; medium = công cụ, phương tiện để thể hiện nghệ thuật</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Attempt 1:</strong> Yes, I do like art. I love to listen to music, read books, and view people's drawings. I think art is a great way to express ourself to other people.</p>\n<p>- Direct answer</p>\n<p>- Listing examples: music, books, drawings</p>\n<p>- Why: Because art is a way to express feeling&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Attempt 2:</strong> Yes, definitely. I have always liked art because it helps me to express myself. I enjoy listening to music, reading novels, and admiring people's paintings. They really inspire and make me think creatively.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- I like -&gt; Thay bằng I enjoy</p>\n<p>- reading books -&gt; reading novels</p>\n<p>- viewing/seeing people's drawing -&gt; admiring people's paintings</p>\n<p>- inspire to think creatively</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>2. Examiner</strong>: Do you think that art classes are important in school?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Candidate</strong>: I feel that art is very subjective. Teaching basic theories about art is sometimes necessary so people can understand concepts like color theory and composition. However, I don’t think following strict methods on how to draw certain things is necessary. Everyone should have the freedom to let their creative mind go in whatever direction they want.</p>\n<p>- art is subjective (nghệ thuật là chủ quan)</p>\n<p>- color theory, composition (the way in which different elements of an artwork are combined)</p>\n<p>- let creative mind go in any direction they want</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Attemp to answer:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Ideas: art help creativity, art help relax after a long hours of focus</p>\n<p>- I believe that art classes are indeed crucial in school because it helps grow creativity and imagination in students, and art also give students a chance to relax after long hours of focus on academic subjects like math or science.</p>\n<p>- Note:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ creativity, imagination</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ give a chance to relax</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ academic subjects</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>3. Examiner: </strong>Who are your favorite artists?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Candidate: In terms of the music industry, my favorite artist is Rihanna. I love her music — every time I put it on in my car, it changes my mood. I also enjoy sharing that experience with my friends. So yes, she’s definitely one of my top favorite artists.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Attempt: My favorite artist is Phan Manh Quynh. He is a Vietnamese singer and also a songwriter. He is famous for many love songs, such as Co Chang Trai Viet Len Cay or Vo Nguoi Ta. I often listen to his song when I playing video games or doing home chores. I really love his unique voice and meaningful lyrics. He is definitely my number one artist.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>4. Examiner</strong>: Now let’s talk about animals. Do you have a pet at home?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Candidate</strong>: I actually have two cats. I love animals, but especially cats — everything about them! One of my cats is called Ni and the other is Tuti. Ni kind of reflects my personality — she’s a bit lazy and introverted, just like me. I really love cats; they’re fluffy, friendly, and I enjoy their company.</p>\n<p>- Direct answer and pic a specific animal: I love animals, but expecially cats - everything about them!</p>\n<p>- Example: One of my cats is called Ni and the other is Tuti.</p>\n<p>- Why love them: I realy love cats because they are fluffy, friendly, and I enjoy their company.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Attempt</strong>: Yes, I do have a dog at home. He is a min pin dog, and his name is Bờm. I enjoy playing with him every time I can, and he is very fast. When we went for a walk, he would run to explore everything around and come back to us right after.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Attempt 2:</strong> Yes I do have a dog at home and his name is Bờm. He is a brown min pin dog and he is very playful and energetic. I love spending time with him whenever I can. Everytime we go out, he gets super excited and run around to explore everything, and then quickly comes back to me. He always make me laugh with his funny little actions.</p>\n<p>- energetic and playful</p>\n<p>- got super excited</p>\n<p>- funny little actions</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>5. Examiner</strong>: Would you like a different pet in the future?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Candidate</strong>: I used to have two ducks, but I had to give them to a shelter because I couldn’t take proper care of them at home. In the future, I’d love to have ducks again, maybe when I’m fully settled in my own house. It would be nice to revisit that memory.</p>\n<p>- Focus on one animal: Ducks</p>\n<p>- Example: Used to have a duck not now</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Attempt</strong>: Maybe when I settle down in my own house, then I would like to have a cat. Despite having a dog as a pet, I always love cats because they look really cute, more than dogs. Back then, when my grandparents used to have cats, I enjoyed hugging them and listening to their purr. That is why I will definitely own a cat someday.</p>\n<p>- Focus on one animals: Cats</p>\n<p>- Example: Used to play with grandparent's cat</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>6. Examiner: </strong>Do you prefer cats or dogs?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Candidate</strong>: Definitely cats! I think it’s partly because I come from a Muslim family, and dogs are often seen as not very clean. So cats have always been the preferred pet in our home. I love everything about them — their personality, their looks, and the way they act.</p>\n<p>- Directly answer: Definitely cats</p>\n<p>- Because dog often seen as not clean in Muslim family</p>\n<p>- Because I love everything about cats, their personality, their looks, and the way they act</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Attempt</strong>: I would say I prefer cats to dogs. I find cats cuter, and I really like their personalities. They're independent, relaxed, and they just live freely without caring too much about others. I think that is pretty cool.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>7. Examiner:</strong> Now let’s talk about reading. How often do you read books?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Candidate</strong>: Back in middle school, I used to be really into books — it was basically my personality! I loved spending time alone just reading, and my family often told me to go outside because I read so much. Even when I did go out, I’d bring a book with me. Recently, I’ve fallen out of the habit because life’s been busy, but I still try to read about once every two months.</p>\n<p>- Useful sentences:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I used to be really into books</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Back in middle school/ Back then in my middle school</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I love spending time alone just reading</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Even when abc, I would xyz</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ I have fallen out of the habit/I have stopped doing it regularly</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Life have been busy</p>\n<p>- Answer in final sentence: I still try to read once every two months.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Attempt</strong>: I used to read books a lot, especially detective books. At my parents' home, I still have books stored in my desk, and if I have a chance to go back home, I would love to read them again. Nowadays, I rarely read because life has been busy, but I would say once every few months I will read a book.</p>\n<p>- Points:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Used to read book</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Now rarely read</p>\n<p>- Example: Have books in parents' home</p>\n<p>- Reason to rarely read: Life has been busy.</p>\n<p>- Feeling: Would love to have time to focus on read agian.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
202510241950161670	https://ieltscity.vn/bai-mau-de-thi-ielts-writing-task-2-ngay-19-10-2025/	<p><strong>Question</strong>: Some people say it is government’s responsibility to transport children to school, while others believe parents should transport their children to school. Discuss both views and give your opinion.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong>:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The question of who should bear the primary responsibility for transporting children to school is a key issue that reflects different views on the roles of the state and the family. While some argue that this should be a governmental service, others maintain that it is part of parental duty. Ultimately, I believe that the most effective solution lies in a shared responsibility, with the government ensuring provision for those most in need.</p>\n<p>- bear the primary responsibility = chịu trách nhiệm</p>\n<p>- reflects different views on the role = phản ánh những góc nhìn về vai trò của ...</p>\n<p>- governmental service = dịch vụ của chính phủ</p>\n<p>- While some argue that ..., others maintain that ...</p>\n<p>- parental duty = trách nhiệm của phụ huynh</p>\n<p>- Ultimately, I believe that ... = Cuối cùng thì, tôi tin rằng</p>\n<p>- the most effective solution</p>\n<p>- lies in = nằm ở</p>\n<p>- shared responsibility = trách nhiệm chung</p>\n<p>- ensuring provision for = đảm bảm cung cấp cho</p>\n<p>- those most in need = những người cần nhất</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Body 1:</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>From the perspective of state responsibility, providing school transport offers clear benefits for <strong>equity</strong> and <strong>traffic management</strong>. <strong>Firstly</strong>, a comprehensive school bus system ensures that all students, particularly those residing in <strong>remote areas</strong> or from <strong>disadvantaged backgrounds</strong>, have <strong>reliable</strong> and safe access to education, thereby upholding the principle of social <strong>equality</strong>. <strong>Secondly</strong>, organized public transport for students <strong>alleviates</strong> traffic congestion during peak hours, which is a common problem in most urban centers. This collective approach is also more environmentally <strong>sustainable</strong> than having thousands of parents drive individual cars.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- From the perspective of = Xét từ quan điểm của ...</p>\n<p>- state responsibility = trách nhiệm của chính phủ</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ state = the whole system of a country</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ government = a part of a state, run by a group of people</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ state = rarely change, example: Việt Nam Cộng Hòa Dân Chủ (1945-1976), Cộng Hòa XHCN VN (1976-nay)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ government = changes by elections</p>\n<p>- clear benefits = lợi ích rõ ràng &lt;&gt; hidden benefits (bonus: direct/indirect benefits)</p>\n<p>- equity = bình đẳng</p>\n<p>- traffic management = quản lý giao thông</p>\n<p>- Firstly ..., Secondly ...</p>\n<p>- comprehensive system = hệ thống toàn diện</p>\n<p>- those residing in remote areas = những ai ở nơi xa</p>\n<p>- disadvantaged backgrounds = có điều kiện khó khăn</p>\n<p>- Thereby &lt;&gt; therefore</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Thereby = by doing that, example: He was hired, thereby he became the youngest employee in the office.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Therefore = as a result, example: He was the best candidate. Therefore, he was hired.</p>\n<p>- the principle of social equality = quy tắc công bằng xã hội</p>\n<p>- organized public transport = giao thông công cộng một cách có tổ chức</p>\n<p>- traffic congestion = sự tắc nghẽn giao thông</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ rush hour, traffic jam</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ heavy traffic</p>\n<p>- peak hours = giờ cao điểm</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ busy hours</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ high-traffic hours</p>\n<p>- in most urban centers = trong đa số các vùng trung tâm đô thị</p>\n<p>- this collective approach = cách tiếp cận mang tính tập thể này</p>\n<p>- enviromentally sustainable = bền vững về mặt môi trường</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Body 2: </strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Conversely, the view that parents should be responsible stems from the fundamental obligation of parental care. Advocates for this view contend that transporting children to school is an <strong>inherent</strong> part of <strong>parenting</strong> and daily family life. <strong>Furthermore</strong>, parental involvement allows for flexibility and often provides opportunities to <strong>nurture</strong> a child’s health through active <strong>commuting</strong>, such as walking or cycling. Assigning this cost and logistical burden entirely to the state may also be seen as an <strong>undue strain</strong> on public finances, potentially diverting funds from core educational programmes.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- From the perspective of ..., Conversely ...</p>\n<p>- should be responsible = nên có trách nhiệm</p>\n<p>- stems from = có nguồn gốc từ ...</p>\n<p>- the fundamental obligation = nghĩa vụ cơ bản</p>\n<p>- parental care = sự chăm sóc của cha mẹ</p>\n<p>- parental involvement = sự có mặt của cha mẹ</p>\n<p>- active commuting = chủ động đi lại</p>\n<p>- Assigning this cost = việc giao toàn bộ chi phí</p>\n<p>- logistical burden = gánh nặng hậu cần</p>\n<p>- undue strain = căng thẳng quá mức</p>\n<p>- public finances = tài chính công</p>\n<p>- potentially diverting funds = có khả năng làm lệch hướng các nguồn vốn ...&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- core educational programmes = các chương trình giáo dục chính</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Conclusion:</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>In conclusion, both sides present valid arguments, but neither perspective is entirely <strong>sustainable</strong> on its own. While parents should be encouraged to take responsibility for local <strong>commuting</strong> and promoting active travel, the government has a crucial role to play in providing transportation as a social <strong>safety net</strong>. Therefore, I maintain that governments must prioritize establishing safe, <strong>subsidized</strong> bus services for long-distance commuters and financially strained families, <strong>whilst</strong> simultaneously encouraging and supporting parents in all other instances.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- both sides present valid arguments = cả hai bên đều có lý</p>\n<p>- neither perspective is entirely sustainable on its own = không có quan điểm nào trong cả hai quan điểm là hoàn toàn bền vững</p>\n<p>- crucial role to play = vai trò quan trọng</p>\n<p>- social safety net = mạng lưới xã hội an toàn</p>\n<p>- subsidized bus services = dịch vụ bus được trợ cấp</p>\n<p>- long-distance commuters = những người đi lại (học tập, làm việc) với khoảng cách xa</p>\n<p>- financial strained families = các gia đình có sự căng thẳng về tài chính</p>\n<p></p>\n
202510271001093295	Describe your favourite actor or actress	<p><strong>Describe your favorite actor or actress.</strong></p>\n<p>You should say:</p>\n<p>- Who the actor or actress is What kind of actor or actress they are</p>\n<p>- What movies/programs they have starred in</p>\n<p>And explain why they are your favorite actor or actress.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>My favorite actor is Keanu Reeves, he is the main character in the famous movie The Matrix in 1999. He often stars/acts in actions and sometimes in science-fiction movies. People might know him from his famous series John Wick, which started in 2014, and I really love this series but The Matrix is still the best.&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>What I really like about him, beside his wonderful acting, is that his personality. He is the coolest actor and he has a good humor, which I can see from interviews with him. Beside being a successful actor, his personal life is heartbreaking because of the loss of his wife and daughter.&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>And I really respect him after I read about his quote "I'm at the stage of my life where I keep myself out of any arguments, even if you tell me 1 + 1 = 5 then you are absolutely correct". This quote shaped my thinking about how to response other people opinions about my life. Also, I believe that he has made many charity donations without announcing the exect amount, because he doesn't need to. He has no scandals at all. And that is it - he is my number one actor.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Ideas</strong>:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- Start with full name, nationality, and basic background</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Keanu Reeves</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Canadian</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Born in Lebanon and grew up in Cananda</p>\n<p>- Mention about first film or first impress</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Matrix in 1999</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Calm but powerful performance</p>\n<p>- Acting style</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ quite character, strong character</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ acting natural</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ humble&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ real and emotional</p>\n<p>- Typical roles</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ main character/stars in</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ romantic, dramatic roles</p>\n<p>- List some popular movies:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ The Matrix in 1999 which is a science fiction movie about the dystopian future</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ John Wick series about a man revenge who kill hist dog</p>\n<p>- Personality and background where I like about the actor:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Charity but not showing off</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Treats people kindly</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Humble, down-to-earth</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Tragic past about the loss of his family</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ Life philosophy, quote...</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Phrases:</p>\n<p>- To begin with, I like his acting.</p>\n<p>- Another reason why I like him is the humble and humor personality</p>\n<p>- What's more that he is not showing off about his charity donations</p>\n<p>- Apart from his acting, I admire his point of view about life</p>\n<p>- I was amazed by the actions that he performed.</p>\n<p>- I really admire how he ...</p>\n<p>- I find him very inspiring because ...</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n
\.
